Def:-
REST APIs is a popular way to build scalable and maintainable backend services. 
REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style,
that defines a set of rules for creating web services, that can be easily consumed by clients. 

REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style,
that uses perform HTTP request. ex: CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations.

HTTP Methods and REST
  GET: Retrieve data (Read).
  POST: Create new data (Create).
  PUT/PATCH: Update existing data (Update).
  DELETE: Remove data (Delete).

1/ Setting up the environment
    mkdir my-rest-api
    cd my-rest-api
    npm init -y

2/ Install Dependencies
   The following packages are commonly used in a REST API:
      Express: is a minimal and flexible web framework for Node.js.
      Mongoose: If you're using MongoDB for your database.
      Cors: To allow Cross-Origin Resource Sharing, enabling your API to be used from different origins.

